caption: Sat outside on an overcast and cool Sunday.  They were willing to put heaters on and gave us blankets to stay warm.  So in general service was good. The veal was tender, swordfish and salmon were soft and juicy. The shrimp pasta had good amount of ingredients. Both chocolate cake and apple crumble were very delicious.

Nice, well-heated outdoor space with great separation between tables for a socially distanced night out to eat. On the pricey side for small portions and the food is hit or miss, but it's nice to get out of the house and feel safe even surrounded by other living beings.

Lia's is a nice restaurant with an innovative and good menu from "Chef Geoff." I usually get the burger (not something I do often at other restaurants), and it's outstanding. This was my second time dining at the restaurant.  The website showed a special that wasn't accurate.  It says $$19.99 meals from 4:00pm-6:30pm weekly.  When I called I was told that wasn't the special and that the website is wrong.  Fix the website then.  The sauce on the crab cakes is extremely rich and has artichokes.  I think the servers should specify what the sauces consist of.  The sauce kept me in the restaurant restroom for about half of my dining experience on Tuesday evening.  Daniel my waitress was absolutely FABULOUS.  He apologized for the menu not reflecting the restaurant was out of Cherry Cobbler and he apologized for not explaining the contents of the sauce too.  I was first introduced to Lia's on Father's day.  I was treated by a friend and my experience was better.  The manager was rough around the edges because they were short staffed I did NOT feel comfortable speaking with him about my concerns.  I will dine there again but I hope some menu/website issues are resolved.

I never write restaurant reviews but today's experience compelled me to do so. Lunch for both of us, a cold soup followed by salmon cakes/salad, hardly could be described as being two courses, as the salmon was served within minutes of the soup. And my plate had at least a whole can of anchovies on it. I like anchovies, but 12 of them on one salad is a bit much. And there was also an uncommon number of capers in the salad, which was soggy with dressing. Then, after we both had finished lunch, we sat talking with empty plates in front of us for about 15 minutes until finally, a member of the wait staff came over to ask whether we had finished. We won't be going back.

Burgers are a great choice as are some of the other items which can be shared. As for the "sit down restaurant" part, our experiences have been a mixed bag, sometimes excellent sometimes not. Those weaker experiences have been either of poor service or poor kitchen execution. I find the bar area a much more reliable choice.

We are easy customer's and nice to wait staff but the service was way below average. 27 minutes to get a drink, and the drink order was wrong 2 times so we finally ordered wine. Still got charged for the drinks that one small sip was taken from! Never took off the bill! We asked and it was ignored. They had my credit card so I did not ask a second time We apologized for having to ask for a drink and bread. 4 people at the table 3 pieces of bread. Received bread, at the 45 minute mark. The wait person kept saying she was there to make our dining experience great but it was insincere and rehearsed not following through with action. Seemed as if we should have been happy to have her but it was simply fake smiles with bad bad service. The sauce on the chicken parm was very sweet with zero character. She asked how the meal was before it arrived! Shrimp scampi mushy with little garlic. The Denison beer was good. I left feeling overcharged and not satisfied with the food and service experience. The location and atmosphere is nice.  We had other items on the check we felt were wrong charged for 9 ounce glasses of wine but was given the 6 ounce glass and pour. Final damage was over 300 with tip and we still tipped well since the staff pouring water actually were good and figured tip sharing.I will never return,too many other places to dine out.  Being charged for the drinks we did not have among other things and such bad service. Never again with this place.

Good burgers

Food here seemed to be very fresh (especially the avocados, which were great); prices are decent for what you get.  The restaurant is very clean and has a very nice, warm décor, and there is plenty of patio space to sit at when the weather is nice.  Overall, I'd probably come back to try some of their non-brunch offerings.
The mushroom pizza is absolutely delicious!

This review's primarily for their happy hour, which is the only thing I've gone to Lia's for. Chef Geoff's sister restaurant has a happy hour all day Monday/Tuesday and the rest of the week (yes, even Saturday and Sunday) from 3-7, where you can get $7 burgers and $9 supermugs. They've also got some pretty solid pizzas, as well -- you can't go wrong with their happy hour menu.
I was able to eat here during restaurant week with a few of my coworkers and we enjoyed it a lot.
Lia's is great for an after-hours cocktail. Not the warmest environment, and a little pricey, but a good place to stop by every few weeks.

Bacon Pizza $15 (5/5 NOMs). Lets have a bacon day, WOW this was a great pizza! I made it an all bacon day :) I just love the bacon and honey mixture. Its like enjoying nice crispy bacon and bang sweet honey flavors hits the tong and nomnom heaven. It was so hard to stop eating it that I totally had far too much. So getting this again!  Smokin' Hog Sidecar $10 (2/5 NOMs). is its smoking? I'm all about trying something weird. Pus if its bacony then I just have to order it. I thought it was very cute that lemon skin was made to look like pig's tail. Not sure if it was such a good idea now. It was very smoky, but not sure I want my drink to be like that. Not something I will try again.  Tempura Espresso Cured Bacon $10 (4/5 NOMs). Oh yea deep fry it, Every wednesday is a bacon bar of awesomeness in here. So if you have a bacon centered thing, I will be there. We started off with some strange bacon appetizer. This bacon that was dip fried goes great with the sweet and sour sauce. Negative point for too much deep fry dough that it kind of overpowered the bacon a bit. The sauce had a great sweet syrupy flavor. I totaly double diped a few times. Will order this again!

While the food was good - with generous portions (at least for the lunch salads) - we ended up waiting far too long for our food while two or three other tables around us were served before us - despite ordering well after we did. Hopefully a one-off, but with the high prices we  probably wont take the chance again any time soon.
Love the cannollis.

Well designed, romantically lit restaurant with nice ambiance. Unbeknownst to us it was restaurant week and were seated at a terrible table next to a server's station.Waitress seemed frazzled and didn't know much about the menu. Her shirt looked like it was going to pop a button. Not enough good options of wines by the glass. The only sparkling they have is a tasteless Cava. The "candy-apple Sangria" tasted like Mayonnaise. Several menu items were sold out. Drink service was slow,food mediocre.My friend's entree came out cold. Unimpressed, though I have been to Lia's a few times before and it was much better on those occasions.
I'd go back just for the crostata.  They're a little disorganized when it comes to honoring reservations. Looks like they have a good early bird special so I will definitely come back.
